wiki.text:
'Franke' is both a surname and a given name. Notable people with the
name include:

'Surname:'
* Bernd Franke, German soccer player
* Bette Franke, Dutch fashion model
* Bob Franke, American folk singer and song writer
* Christian Wilhelm Franke, one of the editors of early editions of the
  Brockhaus Enzyklopädie
* Christopher Franke, German musician/composer in Tangerine Dream
* Egon Franke (fencer) (born 1935), Polish Olympic fencer
* Egon Franke (politician) (1913–1995), German politician
* Garance Franke-Ruta, American writer and editor
* Guillaume Franke, German rugby union player
* Herbert Franke (sinologist) (born 1914), German sinologist, co-author of the
  Cambridge History of China
* Herbert W. Franke, German science fiction writer
* Jay Anthony Franke, American actor, voice actor and musician
* Jens Franke, German mathematician
* Josef Franke (1876–1944), German architect
* Keith Franke (1954–1988), American professional wrestler known as
  Adrian Adonis
* Matthieu Franke, German rugby union player
* Stéphane Franke, German long distance runner
* Victor Franke (1865–1936), German military officer
* Werner Franke, German professor and biologist
* William B. Franke (1894–1979), American financial manager, U.S. Secretary of
  the Navy 1959-1961

'Given name:'
* Franke Previte, American composer
* Franke Rupert (1888–1971), Austrian engraver
